## Episode Lifecycle

```
1. baseline.py: POST /set_task/t1          → sets os.environ["CURRENT_TASK_ID"]
2. client.py: WebSocket connect            → OpenEnv framework calls env.__init__()
3. env.__init__:                           → LAST_ENV_INSTANCE["t1"] = self
4. env.reset():
     data_generator.get_task_data("t1")
       sources["web_forms"]   ──────────→  agent sees this (dirty data)
       hidden_truth["web_forms"] ────────→  GLOBAL_TRUTH_STORE["t1"] (NEVER exposed)

5. Agent Loop (max 15 steps):
     PROFILE_SOURCE         → null counts report
     STANDARDIZE_COLUMN     → LOWERCASE_STRIP / EXTRACT_NUMBERS / TO_DATETIME_ISO
     HANDLE_MISSING         → DROP_ROW or FILL_VALUE
     EXECUTE_SQL            → arbitrary SQL on in-memory SQLite
     DEDUPLICATE            → EXACT_EMAIL or FUZZY_NAME_PHONE
     SUBMIT_PIPELINE        → sets done=True

6. baseline.py: POST /grader/t1
     graders.py fetches LAST_ENV_INSTANCE["t1"]
     graders.py calls get_task_data("t1") → regenerates truth from Faker seed(101)
     evaluate_dataframes():
       pd.merge(truth, agent_output, on="customer_id", how="left")
       All columns: strip().lower() exact match
       score = correct_rows/truth - penalty(0.15/extra row)
```

---

## Pre-Test Risk Flags

> [!IMPORTANT]
> [reset()](file:///C:/Users/ritik/Desktop/CRM-Datapipeline-env/server/environment.py#46-71) in environment.py reads `os.environ["CURRENT_TASK_ID"]`, NOT the `task_id` argument. Always call `POST /set_task/{id}` **before** the WebSocket connection.

> [!WARNING]
> Grader regenerates truth with `Faker.seed(101)`. If [data_generator.py](file:///C:/Users/ritik/Desktop/CRM-Datapipeline-env/server/data_generator.py) seed ever changes, grader and environment will produce mismatched datasets and every score will be wrong.

> [!TIP]
> [grade_task_2](file:///C:/Users/ritik/Desktop/CRM-Datapipeline-env/server/graders.py#60-64) expects `env.get_final_dataframe("merged_output")`. The agent's SQL or MERGE action **must** write to a table named exactly `merged_output`. The T2/T3 smart fallback in [baseline.py](file:///c:/Users/ritik/Desktop/CRM-Datapipeline-env/baseline.py) is not yet implemented — add before final demo.
